TopicTitle: Stock Parts Missing from Un-modded Install

Articles.Content:
Hey guys,

Apologies if this problem has been already posted elsewhere but I seem to be having an issue with some of the stock parts not loading in a completely un-modded version of KSP.

Here are the credentials:

KSP Version: build id = 006422014-10-07_12-12-01

Branch: master

Version: 0.25.0

Basically I had the mods FusTek Station Parts, MechJeb and Kethane installed. Tried playing on an old-ish save (maybe 2 months old) and noticed that the MKII cockpit was acting weird; like when I tried to use one of them in the VAB it would show as being kinda blurry. So I backed up my game folder via Steam, completely deleted the entirety of the game via Steam/Steamapps as well as deleting local content for the game via Steam. I then went and reinstalled KSP via Steam and even though none of the addons are there any more, I seem to still be missing some parts which are stock in the game (such as the orange tanks, structural pylons and large docking adapters.) This is while playing in Sandbox mode and I haven't even got my backup file plugged back in.

System Spec:

AMD Phenom II X6 1100T running at stock 3.3 Ghz

12.0 Gb Ram

64-Bit Windows 7 Ultimate

Running on a 2Tb WD SATA HDD with 1 TB of free space

Please help me! I need to get more Kerbals onto distant planets!

Hmm unusual, if you do a cache verification in Steam it should see there's missing files and redownload those for you, I'm not sure what else to suggest at this point though.

Your output_log.txt should show if there's any in-game errors, see the stickies for more info

Definately, 120% a Sandbox game. Not imported from the backed-up save; there is no saved games in the resume game list! I did notice though; I removed and reinstalled KSP for like the fourth time and whilst I was removing it, I also deleted any files that contained "Kerbal" by searching for them via the Start menu. Once I'd done that and reinstalled, several parts (not all of them) reappeared in the spawn menu of the VAB so I think it must be a file duplication problem more than anything.

Is there any way to search for associated files for KSP or, could someone please tell me what file types I should be searching for to make sure I can carry out a clean, clean, CLEAAAANNNN install?! lol
Managed to sort it - I had a sneaky backup saved on my external USB drive that seemed to be causing some kind of conflict. Deleted that and it's fine now!
